abstract: Brian Wilson, a Beach Boys co-founder, asked fans to join him in signing a petition protesting the group’s performance at the conference. Donald Trump Jr., an avid hunter, was a scheduled speaker and is part of an auction for a hunt in Alaska.
snippet: Brian Wilson, a Beach Boys co-founder, asked fans to join him in signing a petition protesting the group’s performance at the conference. Donald Trump Jr., an avid hunter, was a scheduled speaker and is part of an auction for a hunt in Alaska.
lead_paragraph: A hunting conference in Reno, Nev., this week was drawing online protests, with Brian Wilson, a co-founder of the Beach Boys, asking fans to join him in signing a petition protesting the group’s performance on Wednesday.

abstract: Encouraged by the murky results in Iowa, Mr. Bloomberg is also expanding his field staff as he tries to win the Democratic primary by ignoring the first four states. “Those are old rules,” he said.
snippet: Encouraged by the murky results in Iowa, Mr. Bloomberg is also expanding his field staff as he tries to win the Democratic primary by ignoring the first four states. “Those are old rules,” he said.
lead_paragraph: COMPTON, Calif. — Michael R. Bloomberg’s presidential campaign moved on Tuesday to exploit the chaotic outcome of the Iowa caucuses, escalating an already enormous campaign of television advertising and publicly making the case that a messy outcome in the early states opened the way for Mr. Bloomberg.

abstract: At Simon & Schuster, best sellers were her stock in trade. She popularized the nonfiction political page turner, starting with “All the President’s Men.”
snippet: At Simon & Schuster, best sellers were her stock in trade. She popularized the nonfiction political page turner, starting with “All the President’s Men.”
lead_paragraph: Alice Mayhew, a widely admired editor who shepherded into print best sellers by a veritable who’s who of writers — along the way popularizing the Washington political narrative, beginning with “All the President’s Men” in 1974 — died on Tuesday at her home in Manhattan. She was 87.

abstract: Only a handful of states and territories will try to pick the Democratic nominee with similar practices as Iowa, where officials faced delays and problems reporting results.
snippet: Only a handful of states and territories will try to pick the Democratic nominee with similar practices as Iowa, where officials faced delays and problems reporting results.
lead_paragraph: As Iowa grapples with the aftermath of a Democratic caucus that one party leader called a “systemwide disaster,” American voters and election officials are already looking ahead at the handful of other states and American territories that will be picking — or trying to pick — the Democratic nominee in similar ways.

abstract: The Maine senator became the latest Republican to condemn President Trump’s conduct but argue it did not warrant his removal.
snippet: The Maine senator became the latest Republican to condemn President Trump’s conduct but argue it did not warrant his removal.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Senator Susan Collins, Republican of Maine, said on Tuesday that she would vote to acquit President Trump of abuse of power and obstruction of Congress, calling his conduct “wrong” but saying she could not support removing him from office.

abstract: Partial results for the caucuses were released, and the confusion continued to reverberate around the presidential race.
snippet: Partial results for the caucuses were released, and the confusion continued to reverberate around the presidential race.
lead_paragraph: Mr. Buttigieg took a narrow early lead over Mr. Sanders in the first wave of partial results from the caucuses. Ms. Warren was in third place and Mr. Biden was in fourth.
